<date>1543378685934<//date>< review>
This place has changed ownership so some of the past reviews might not be so good. But the new owner has turned Wes's back around to what it was years ago. I love this little feed store. I  go  when I need things like hay or Timothy Hay or some feed for wild birds or chickens. On this trip I went for hay dor my manger scene. I was able to buy part of a bale, (one bale would have been $8, not a lot of money but I didn't need a whole bale of hay) While I was there I noticed he didn't have any chickens for sale. The owner told me that a disease has hit the southern California area, Virulent Newcastle Disease (VND) (it is deadly to birds especially chickens and is very contagious) so he can't sell chicks until December. Great service, friendly people, small and interesting. It's local kind of business that I really love.</review>

After eight years of problems with the skin on my face and around my eye area and having many doctors tell me they weren't sure what was wrong I finally found out what my problem was. Dr. Meadows examined me and told me I needed a patch test for contact dermatitis. I can't believe that after so many other doctors including eye doctors no one had a clue. It turned out that I am allergic to many things that I put on my hands and face. They also gave me a printout of everything. I have started to change what I use and finally I am getting relief without using a bunch of medicines that have bad side effects. This is a great place!< /review>

We followed Dr. Ashley from another local holistic vet practice because she's got such great integrity with our pet. We (Aaron and Rosalie) first met Dr. Ashley when she started working at Creature Comforts (another great, integrative veterinary practice that combines the best of traditional and integrative veterinary medicine in the upper Fruitvale of Oakland). She spent time attending to our beloved cat-son, Ralphie, when he was near the end of his life. She didn‚Äôt take any unnecessary measures in her treatment of him, and she utilized both new modalities (such as prescribing fortifying herbs, laser heat treatments, etc.) as well as more traditional ones (including recommending that we modify his diet). After our visits and phone call consultations, we came away impressed that Dr. Ashley knew a wide variety of treatments to choose from. When a treatment was not providing a desired outcome, she knew others that we could try, both to prolong Ralphie‚Äôs life (we are convinced that under her care, Ralphie lived far longer than had he gone to a veterinarian who practiced just one modality of medical care) but also to maintain (and, in some cases, improve) his quality of life. She also spent time checking-in with us, asking how we were doing and coping, not only with Ralphie‚Äôs ongoing illness, but also with the other stressors in our everyday lives. Consequently, we felt that our visits to take Ralphie to be treated by her were a lot less stressful than they might have been, had they not been with someone as caring and understanding as she.

When we learned that she was establishing an independent practice in our town of Alameda, we were very glad to hear that more people would have an opportunity to benefit from her wide-ranging and in-depth veterinary knowledge and generosity of spirit.

We wish her every success!</text>

I have used every FedEx location in West LA, Santa Monica, and Marina Del Rey for personal and work- this location is by far the best location to ship packages from.

<date>1543461022498<//date><Rate>5</Rate>< text>
I go out of my way in 40 minutes of traffic to go to this place. I get a straightforward men's haircut for $6 and it's done better and with more care than places that charge 20. I went in for my regular haircut today but didn't make it until 10 minutes before closing time and expected it might be a hassle, but it wasn't. They sat me without question, had a smile on their face, and I didn't feel like they skimped on the quality or anything. They speak mostly Vietnamese here, but I'm a white guy and don't feel off put or out of place here. It's surprisingly nice and spacious and well lit. If you're a guy looking for a basic haircut, I can't recommend this place enough.</text>

<user_name>Srq Auto</user_name>< review>
Our Dealership has gone through multiple CRM and DMS platforms in the past 3 years from Auto Manager to Wayne Reaves to Dominion to DealerTrack back to Wayne Reaves and now we are using the Dealer Center DMS and CRM AIO platform. While we are in the early stages of using this new system, I must commend all involved who put this software together. The flow and navigation of inputting customer information to penciling a deal to submitting the deal to lenders thru Dealer Center with the ability of opening the deal up in DealerTrack as well, is impressive to say the least.

Of course with any system there will be learning curves, however; help has been a phone call away. Saul Vasquez; our support rep, has been professional, expedient and most importantly has resolved every issue that has arisen thus far.

At a fraction of the cost of most other DMS and CRM software programs available today the "juice is worth the squeeze" when it comes to using the Dealer Center AIO system.

Jim Schumacher
SRQ Auto, LLC< /review>

< review>
I am very happy with Dealercenter.   I have been in this industry for over 30 years, and have worked with all types of dealerships from large independents to multi-point franchises and one thing I've noticed, is that most dealerships use a myriad of disparate applications to manage their DMS, Inventory and marketing needs.  Because of this, inevitably, dealers find themselves running their day to day business with cumbersome, redundant and sometimes even counterproductive systems.  What Dealercenter does for the small dealership, is to bring all the tools I need to compete with the larger dealerships while my support team at Dealercenter handles the technical issues I don't have time to manage.  I definitely recommend Dealercenter to any independent dealership not in direct competition with me.</review>

<Text>As that finance manager and specifically working on our internet marketing efforts with my background been in computers I am always looking to see how to improve the use of computer systems to help streamline operations. When it cam to following up on leads obtained from various sources the dealership had been doing so manually. leads were received via email. The leads were then printed out and an attempt to follow-up on them was made. Then came the hard part, organizing the follow-up process. Determining if someone had contacted the prospect or not. The worst part was that during all this time the dealership had access and was paying for the CRM portion of the DealerCenter system but were not using it.

The dealership was even contemplating to cancel the CRM option form the current package. During this time we had started talks on centralizing all leads into one platform, finding a way to make it possible for all of us involved to see what was going on with all prospects.

It was here that we made contact with an amazing person "Monica" at DealerCenter. Monica provided me at first with an introduction to the CRM and I clearly saw that this was what we needed to implement. It has been an amazing ride. I have now been able to get everyone to use the CRM, We have all of our lead providers feeding the leads to the DealerCenter CRM. The staff is exited and loves the CRM. Having the ability to send text messages, emails and have all the information in one place and available with just a click is just AMAZING. The mobile application is an incredible tool.

Just to think that we were about to cancel access to the CRM because we were paying for something we did not use and thought we were wasting money on it.

Wow, how wrong was that thought. This CRM has now become the one of the most important features for us in the DealerCenter system.

Thank you again Monica you have given us the tool we were looking for to manage this important portion of our operation. Dealers need to know about this amazing part of the system. Like us I am sure there are plenty of dealers out there that are just not aware of the how amazing the CRM work. I strongly recommend the CRM to all dealers. If you are looking to centralize your information for your prospects, leads, customers this is the way to go. I know we will be using it on a daily basis from know on. I also know that we would have made a big mistake if would have cancelled the CRM portion of this system. Awesome job Monica. Thank you.<//Text><user>117557829932673805007< /user>< user_name>
